I saw this suggestion already posted in this group and mentioned it as 
my second approach to resolve this issue. However, my problem with this 
approach is that it generates reports in the &quot;todir&quot; which must be 
viewed separately from the test process. Granted the reports may contain 
exactly the information I&#39;m looking for, but I&#39;d prefer immediate 
feedback when running the tests from ant. That way, I can remain in the 
shell when frequently repeating the test and fix combination.

I hope I missed something about the junitreport target and that I can 
indeed use it to display the text output in a readable format in the 
shell. Please let me know if this is possible.

Shane Duan wrote:
&gt; Have you taken a look at the &#39;junitreport&#39; task?  It can take the file
&gt; set you pass in and generate report.
&gt;  
&gt; So basically, you can use xml report to generate xml file on each test
&gt; case class, then use the junitreport to group the ones you want
&gt; to go together for the report.  We are doing that so that we can
&gt; generate report based on each personl&#39;s reponsible packages.  Then we
&gt; can also use a file set that includes all the xml files as the overall
&gt; test report.  Here is a brief sample:
&gt;  
&gt;   &lt;target name=&quot;personalReport&quot;&gt;
&gt;     &lt;junitreport&gt;
&gt;       &lt;fileset refid=&quot;test.id&quot;/&gt;
&gt;       &lt;report format=&quot;frames&quot; todir=&quot;${reports.tests}/${user}&quot;/&gt;
&gt;     &lt;/junitreport&gt;
&gt;   &lt;/target&gt;
&gt; 
&gt;   &lt;target name=&quot;shaneReport&quot; description=&quot;Shane&#39;s test reports&quot;&gt;
&gt;     &lt;fileset id=&quot;id&quot; dir=&quot;${reports.tests}&quot;&gt;
&gt;       &lt;include name=&quot;TEST-package1.package2.TestCaseClass.xml&quot;/&gt;
&gt;       &lt;include name=&quot;TEST-package1.package3.*.xml&quot;/&gt;
&gt;       &lt;include name=&quot;TEST-package2.package4.xml&quot;/&gt;
&gt;     &lt;/fileset&gt;
&gt;     &lt;antcall target=&quot;personalReport&quot;&gt;
&gt;       &lt;param name=&quot;user&quot; value=&quot;shane&quot;/&gt;
&gt;       &lt;reference refid=&quot;id&quot; torefid=&quot;test.id&quot;/&gt;
&gt;     &lt;/antcall&gt;
&gt;   &lt;/target&gt;
&gt;  
&gt; Hope this is helps.
&gt;  
&gt; Shane
&gt; 
